{
  "texts": [
    "To be more precise, we additionally evaluate the effect of frame shuffling on a subset of temporal questions whose answers are related to content ordering, and intuitively, should be more sensitive to frame shuffling.",
    "The results in Fig. 13 show that shuffling frames again affects little the model performances in answering even temporal questions.",
    "This reflects that the models are stubborn and are not anchored on content order for answering temporal questions.",
    "Combining with our previous observation on BlindQA experiments (see Sec. 3.5 and Fig.",
    "5), we conclude that existing Video-LLMs do not really capture video temporality though they ground on videos for answer predictions."
  ]
}